content:
Create parent-child relationships between assets to represent products with multiple components. This is useful when your business sells a product that has individual parts, such as tent poles, which customers may misplace.

To create hierarchical relationships between assets, use the Parent Asset field and the Child Assets related list on asset detail pages. Assets also have additional fields related to hierarchies:

*   The read-only Root Asset field lists the top-level asset in an asset hierarchy.
*   The read-only Asset Level field is a number that reflects the asset’s position in a hierarchy.

An asset hierarchy can have up to 10,000 assets and be used in various ways to improve your support process. For example:

*   When creating a work order to repair a broken asset, create line items on the work order that correspond to specific child assets.
*   Set up a workflow rule or process that creates a work order line item for each child asset when a work order is created from an asset.

To view an expanded tree grid of all assets in an asset’s hierarchy, click View Asset Hierarchy in the drop-down action menu on any asset detail page. This view gives field service workers a way to quickly identify parts and understand how assets are related to each other. The View Asset Hierarchy action is available only for hierarchies of 500 or fewer assets.
title: Asset Hierarchies in Salesforce
